title: Number of hospitals in Finland 2007 to 2017
summary: Overall Number of hospitals has decreased over the Year.
Number of hospitals is slightly decreasing from 2011 to 2012, and finally roughly constant from 2012 to 2013.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2011 and 2012.
Maximum Number of hospitals, about 275.0 was reported at Year 2011
Minimum Number of hospitals about 259.0 was reached at Year 2013
